    Scope and Contents
MENTAL HEALTH CARE PROJECT 
DeLong, former attendant and manager of the laundry at the Jacksonville State Hospital, recalls her employment in the hospital's laundry, patients working in the laundry as therapy, conditions at the hospital for patients and employees, living conditions for employees on the hospital grounds, conditions at the hospital during the Depression and WWII, a fire at the hospital, and new facilities. 1 tape, 46 mins., 25 pp. 
Interview by Rodger Streitmatter, 1972 
